oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Terminal Station
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Interior view of the Terminal Station in Chattanooga, taken on the concourse area showing the doors leading to the main waiting room area.

The photo appears to have been taken prior to when the station was opened on December 1, 1909. Construction of the station cost a total of $1,500,000. Donn Barber from New York City was the station's architect and designed the station in the Beaux-Arts-style.
